news.title: Asset monetisation plan of Mormugao port faces setbacks
news.para: ​Plans to lease out 50,000 sqm of prime land for warehousing and for a hotel in the port town, as well as a proposal to outsource the Deepvihar Primary School, the 100-bedded hospital, and the old administrative building for 30 years, failed.

news.title: NCLT approves Kingmaker Developers' amalgamation with Real Gem Buildtech
news.para: On November 6, 2023, DB Realty had executed a share purchase agreement to dispose off its 100% stake in equity and preference shares in Real Gem Buildtech for a consideration of approximately Rs 231.42 crore to Kingmaker Developers.

news.title: Macrotech Developers exploring to enter Delhi-NCR: Abhishek Lodha, MD
news.para: "We are exploring to enter Delhi-NCR housing market," he told PTI in an interview. Macrotech Developers is looking to acquire lands, either outright or joint development agreement with landowners, he added.

news.title: Anant Raj posts 54% increase in net profit to Rs 110.32 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 543.97 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal year, from Rs 401.02 crore in the corresponding period of the preceding financial year, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to redevelop project in Lokhandwala, Mumbai
news.para: The project offers a gross development value (GDV) of approximately Rs 950 crore. This is Mahindra Lifespaces' fourth redevelopment project in Mumbai.

news.title: How Noida authority plans to earn from underutilised infrastructure projects
news.para: "These projects have remained underutilised for various reasons. We cannot afford to waste public funds. So, we have decided to repurpose them and generate revenue that can be reinvested for the city's development," said Lokesh M, CEO, Noida authority.

news.title: Sonakshi Sinha sells apartment in Mumbai for Rs 22.50 crore
news.para: The same apartment was bought by Sonakshi Sinha in March 2020 for Rs 14 crore, reflecting a 61% appreciation in value since the purchase.

news.title: Mohali civic body issues notices to 80 building owners for furnishing requisite clearances, NOC
news.para: Notices were issued by the MC commissioner, asking the owners to produce documents within 15 days or face the resumption of plots or demolition of unauthorised structures. The move comes in the wake of Sohana building collapse.

news.title: Pune: Nigdi, Katraj metro extension plans gather steam with Rs 839 crore allocation
news.para: Maha Metro is looking forward to using a maximum portion of funds for the PCMC-Nigdi and Swargate-Katraj extensions, besides completing what remains of the phase-1 routes.

news.title: RWA urges Noida authority to take action as shanties encroach green belt
news.para: Dr. Tarsem Chandra, RWA president of Sector 12, suggested reporting the matter to the police, stating that similar encroachments are occurring across the city.

news.title: Experts raise concerns over Odisha government's plan to eliminate layout plan approval for selling plots
news.para: ​"In order to make one thing right, which is paving the way for smooth registration of plots, the govt is likely to make another major mistake. This will lead to unplanned development in cities," real estate expert Bimalendu Pradhan said.

news.title: Telangana government set to auction Rajiv Swagruha properties
news.para: While the total value of the properties is estimated at over Rs 3,200 crore, only those free of legal disputes will be sold.

news.title: FPCE hails Rs 15,000 crore SWAMIH fund, wants ban on defaulting builders
news.para: Forum For People's Collective Efforts (FPCE) President Abhay Upadhyay said, "SWAMIH Fund 2 is certainly a step much needed. As stated by the FM that this will help in completing additional 1 lakh dwelling units."

news.title: Input tax credit removal set to hit commercial real estate companies
news.para: A retrospective amendment, which comes into effect from July 1, 2017, debars entities, such as commercial real estate companies from claiming ITC on construction costs for their rental buildings.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body doubles fees for plan documents
news.para: Fees for measurement sheets also doubled, from Rs 500 to Rs 1,000. Final plot F forms now cost Rs 500 (up from Rs 300), and zoning certificates are Rs 500 (up from Rs 300).

news.title: Kolkata: NKDA hosts property tax assistance camp in New Town
news.para: The camp will continue till March 31 on the ground floor of the NKDA administrative building in Action Area ID.

news.title: Jaipur development body starts work to develop Rajasthan’s first land pooling scheme
news.para: Officials said that this scheme was made keeping in mind the interests of farmers or landholders, in which for the first time a provision was made to give 45% land to farmers or landholders in exchange for acquisition.

news.title: NGT asks Ludhiana civic body chief to explain non-compliance with orders on illegal structures
news.para: The NGT, in its final orders on July 4, 2024, directed the MC to remove the illegal structures and encroachments from green belts situated in Sarabha Nagar and Model Town Extension in two months.

news.title: CMRL allocates Rs 154 crore for acquiring land for metro rail project in Coimbatore
news.para: The city corporation will soon carry out a land plan survey for the land acquisition with the help of CMRL officials, while the revenue department officials will carry out the land acquisition work.

news.title: Apartments completed before Feb 25, 2017 are eligible for registration: Odisha government
news.para: In a notification released on Saturday, the department confirmed that apartments completed before Feb 25, 2017, remain eligible for registration under the current Act.
